UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0378426683900419
AB  - Models of compensating balance decisions to date have implied that agreed-upon balances are not violated by borrowers. When compensating balance requirements can be deficient, the customer and bank must agree in advance what deficiency fee will be charged. This paper develops boundary conditions for such fees, both with and without lines of credit and with balance requirements on unused lines. This process uncovers a number of important attributes of such fees including dependence upon customer borrowing alternatives, situations of fee impossibility, and elements of practical application.
